        <section title="Examples">

            <section title="XQuery Examples">
            
                <p>The examples here demonstrate eXist's new XQuery processing
                    features. eXist provides two alternatives to execute a single
                    XQuery script in a web application: a generator for Cocoon,
                    called <b>XQueryGenerator</b>, and a servlet, implemented in
                    class <b>XQueryServlet</b>. The XQueryGenerator passes the
                    generated output of the XQuery script as a SAX stream into the
                    Cocoon pipeline. The servlet is configured to respond to
                    requests ending with the suffix <code>.xql</code>.</p>
                
                <p>Both alternatives, the XQueryGenerator as well as the servlet,
                    keep the compiled XQuery script in a cache. The code will only
                    be recompiled if the source file has changed.</p>
                
